<body>
    <h1>Chapter 1: Basics of Derivatives - MCQs</h1>

    <ol>
        <li>
            <h3>51. Which of the following is a unique characteristic of the over-the-counter (OTC) derivatives market?</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>(a) Standardized contracts</li>
                <li>(b) Centralized clearing</li>
                <li class="answer">(c) Negotiated terms and conditions</li>
                <li>(d) Public price dissemination</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>52. What is the primary reason for the introduction of futures contracts?</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>(a) To increase market volatility</li>
                <li>(b) To eliminate counterparty risk</li>
                <li class="answer">(c) To overcome the limitations of forward contracts</li>
                <li>(d) To provide customized derivative solutions</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>53. Which of the following is NOT a potential risk of derivatives trading?</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>(a) Market risk</li>
                <li>(b) Liquidity risk</li>
                <li>(c) Operational risk</li>
                <li class="answer">(d) Inflation risk</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>54. What is the role of the Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) in the derivatives market?</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>(a) To set prices of derivatives contracts</li>
                <li>(b) To guarantee settlement of trades</li>
                <li class="answer">(c) To regulate the market and protect investors</li>
                <li>(d) To provide investment advice to market participants</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>55. What is the significance of the "Tulip Mania" event in the history of derivatives?</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>(a) It demonstrated the success of futures markets</li>
                <li class="answer">(b) It highlighted the risks of speculative bubbles</li>
                <li>(c) It led to the regulation of derivatives trading</li>
                <li>(d) It introduced the concept of option contracts</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>56. Which of the following is NOT a factor contributing to the growth of the derivatives market?</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>(a) Increased market volatility</li>
                <li>(b) Globalization of financial markets</li>
                <li>(c) Technological advancements</li>
                <li class="answer">(d) Decreasing investor awareness</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>57. What is the primary purpose of the "Varma Committee" in the Indian derivatives market?</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>(a) To introduce new derivative products</li>
                <li>(b) To promote derivatives trading among retail investors</li>
                <li class="answer">(c) To recommend risk containment measures</li>
                <li>(d) To educate market participants about derivatives</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>58. Which of the following is a potential drawback of exchange-traded derivatives?</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>(a) Lack of transparency</li>
                <li>(b) Counterparty risk</li>
                <li class="answer">(c) Limited customization</li>
                <li>(d) High transaction costs</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>59. What is the relationship between derivatives and the underlying asset?</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>(a) Derivatives have a fixed value, regardless of the underlying asset</li>
                <li>(b) Derivatives always move in the opposite direction of the underlying asset</li>
                <li class="answer">(c) Derivatives derive their value from the underlying asset</li>
                <li>(d) Derivatives have no relationship with the underlying asset</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>60. Which of the following is NOT a common type of derivative used in India?</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>(a) Index futures</li>
                <li>(b) Stock options</li>
                <li class="answer">(c) Credit Default Swaps (CDS)</li>
                <li>(d) Interest Rate Swaps</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>
